FBIS4-48158 "drafr093_e_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 WEST AFRICA Liberia Taylor Appeals to LNTG To Form National Army Taylor Appeals to LNTG To Form National Army AB1205180894 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1200 GMT 12 May 94 AB1205180894 Gbarnga Radio ELRL English BFN [Text] The commander in chief of the NPFL [National Patriotic Front of Liberia], former President Charles Gankay Taylor, has called on the LNTG [Liberian National Transitional Government] to arrange for the formation of a national army to take charge of the security of the country. President Taylor has proposed that all factions should provide soldiers for the formation of the new army. He said leaving the security of the country solely in the hands of a foreign army could threaten the national security interests of Liberia.
